If your symptoms don't resolve in after completion of medication please return to clinic for further screening., UTI - Comment Only ·Instructions: make sure to finish out antibioticsYou have been diagnosed with a urinary tract infection, please make sure to complete your full course of antibiotics. A sample of your urine has been sent to the lab for a urine culture which will determine what type of bacteria is causing your symptoms.If your symptoms don't resolve in 3 to 5 days, please follow up for further screening.Make sure to drink plenty of water, make sure to urinate after intercourse, and avoid holding your urine., brief (1-3 elements), Avery Ramsey is a 32 Years Old Male ( DOB 07/04/1987)report burning with urination and penile discharge for several dayswas diagnosed with an UTI 1 month ago and did not finish the antibioticsalso wants STD testingreports having unprotected sex with 1 partner , No, No, No, No, No, brief (1-3 elements), I called this patient today to initiate a telehealth appointment but there was no answer.
